HEADWORD: Jerker
<hw>Jerk"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A beater.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. &
Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who jerks or moves with a jerk.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A North American river chub
(<spn>Hybopsis biguttatus</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Jerkin</ent>⟦br⟧
